00:10:59.575 --> 00:11:02.370
How old were you when you
started out auditioning?

00:11:02.370 --> 00:11:04.830
- 14.
- In Kentucky?

00:11:04.830 --> 00:11:05.706
- No, New York.

00:11:05.706 --> 00:11:07.500
- In New York?
- Yeah.

00:11:07.500 --> 00:11:09.085
- 14?
- 14.

00:11:09.085 --> 00:11:10.544
- I was 12.

00:11:10.544 --> 00:11:11.879
- Wow.
- Yeah.

00:11:11.879 --> 00:11:14.757
And you did a lot of commercials, TV-

00:11:14.757 --> 00:11:16.133
- Yeah.
- Before "Winter's Bone?"

00:11:16.133 --> 00:11:17.468
- And we were both on sitcoms.

00:11:17.468 --> 00:11:18.803
- Yes.

00:11:18.803 --> 00:11:19.970
What was your sitcom again?

00:11:19.970 --> 00:11:21.347
- Well, yours was "Growing Pains"

00:11:21.347 --> 00:11:22.181
- Mine was "Growing Pains"
- Which I watched

00:11:22.181 --> 00:11:23.599
every day after school.

00:11:23.599 --> 00:11:25.142
And mine was "The Billing Bowl Show,"

00:11:25.142 --> 00:11:27.228
which I don't think anybody has ever seen

00:11:27.228 --> 00:11:28.479
except me and my parents.

00:11:29.730 --> 00:11:31.190
- How long were you on it?

00:11:31.190 --> 00:11:32.024
- Two years.

00:11:32.024 --> 00:11:32.858
- Two years?

00:11:32.858 --> 00:11:35.027
- And then as soon as I
wrapped "Winter's Bone"

00:11:35.027 --> 00:11:37.822
and then it, the show got canceled.

00:11:37.822 --> 00:11:38.781
It worked perfectly.

00:11:38.781 --> 00:11:40.866
- I did one year of "Growing Pains,"

00:11:40.866 --> 00:11:42.868
then I got "This Boy's Life,"

00:11:42.868 --> 00:11:44.495
which was like my first starring role.

00:11:44.495 --> 00:11:46.497
And they were so incredibly awesome to me

00:11:46.497 --> 00:11:49.250
because I think that we
were gonna do another year,

00:11:49.250 --> 00:11:52.128
and the late, great Alan Thicke
and all of them got together

00:11:52.128 --> 00:11:54.213
and like, "Let the kid go do this,

00:11:54.213 --> 00:11:55.047
let 'em go."
- Oh

00:11:55.047 --> 00:11:57.049
- It was really an amazing moment.

00:11:57.049 --> 00:11:58.008
They were so sweet.
- Yeah, they're not normally

00:11:58.008 --> 00:11:59.301
nice like that.

00:11:59.301 --> 00:12:01.929
- And what was your first commercial?

00:12:01.929 --> 00:12:06.642
- I did an MTV promo for
"My Super Sweet 16," a show.

00:12:07.935 --> 00:12:09.395
So I was like on a Shay's lounge, like,

00:12:09.395 --> 00:12:10.438
and then they like dropped me.

00:12:10.438 --> 00:12:11.397
- But were you in the show

00:12:11.397 --> 00:12:13.482
"Super Sweet 16?"
- No,

00:12:13.482 --> 00:12:14.942
I don't have the money.
- What is a promo?

00:12:14.942 --> 00:12:15.776
What does that mean?

00:12:15.776 --> 00:12:19.697
- A promo is like, it's like
a commercial for the show.

00:12:19.697 --> 00:12:20.531
- Still don't get it.

00:12:20.531 --> 00:12:21.449
- Okay.

00:12:21.449 --> 00:12:24.744
I was playing a rich girl.

00:12:24.744 --> 00:12:26.370
- I see.
- Having a,

00:12:26.370 --> 00:12:27.496
over the top birthday.
- You're acting.

00:12:27.496 --> 00:12:28.330
- I was acting.

00:12:28.330 --> 00:12:30.374
- You were acting.
- Like I had money.

00:12:30.374 --> 00:12:31.542
- Gotcha.

00:12:31.542 --> 00:12:32.793
(Leonardo and Jennifer laughing)

00:12:32.793 --> 00:12:35.212
- Mine was a-
- You didn't grow up rich?

00:12:35.212 --> 00:12:36.088
- No.

00:12:36.088 --> 00:12:39.008
- But you got a sitcom
at 12, I mean that's-

00:12:39.008 --> 00:12:42.803
- Yeah, I mean I think a lot
of my propulsion to want to act

00:12:42.803 --> 00:12:44.388
was to get out of my neighborhood.

00:12:44.388 --> 00:12:45.347
- Mm.

00:12:45.347 --> 00:12:48.392
- Like that? You could do that for work.

00:12:48.392 --> 00:12:49.643
- Right.
- My stepbrother

00:12:49.643 --> 00:12:51.145
did a lot of commercials,
I was like, wait a minute,

00:12:51.145 --> 00:12:52.688
you could get paid to do that?

00:12:52.688 --> 00:12:54.231
- Yeah.

00:12:54.231 --> 00:12:56.066
- I'm gonna get, I gotta
get out of this place?

00:12:56.066 --> 00:12:56.901
Yes.

00:12:56.901 --> 00:12:59.403
So I was the stage mom.

00:12:59.403 --> 00:13:00.988
- Right.

00:13:00.988 --> 00:13:03.532
- I was pushing my parents
to take me on auditions.

00:13:03.532 --> 00:13:06.577
I'm like, you know, my
school is this far away,

00:13:06.577 --> 00:13:09.205
when you pick me up we can
stop at a couple auditions

00:13:09.205 --> 00:13:10.039
on the way home-
- Yeah.

00:13:10.039 --> 00:13:11.999
- Get me out there.

00:13:11.999 --> 00:13:15.169
And then I, like I said, my stepbrother,

00:13:15.169 --> 00:13:16.337
he was an actor,

00:13:16.337 --> 00:13:19.340
did an episode of "Battlestar Galactica"

00:13:19.340 --> 00:13:22.134
and some television, and I was like,

00:13:22.134 --> 00:13:24.178
if anything, this is
gonna be my college fund

00:13:24.178 --> 00:13:26.055
to get me money to try to have

00:13:26.055 --> 00:13:28.015
some sort of career in something.

00:13:28.974 --> 00:13:31.185
And then I didn't book
anything for a while,

00:13:31.185 --> 00:13:35.523
I got a Matchbox car commercial
where I played a gangster

00:13:35.523 --> 00:13:36.857
with slicked back hair.

00:13:36.857 --> 00:13:37.858
- Wow.

00:13:37.858 --> 00:13:39.985
- Like I had a briefcase
and I opened it up.

00:13:39.985 --> 00:13:43.656
- Did you go to the audition
looking like a gangster?

00:13:43.656 --> 00:13:44.907
- Yes.

00:13:44.907 --> 00:13:46.742
I slicked back my hair.

00:13:46.742 --> 00:13:49.370
I put like a little leather jacket on.

00:13:49.370 --> 00:13:52.122
And then I got a lot
of Mickey Safety Club,

00:13:54.875 --> 00:13:57.461
they were called afterschool
special kind of things

00:13:57.461 --> 00:13:59.421
where you teach kids not
to do drugs and all that,

00:13:59.421 --> 00:14:02.007
and the dangers of drugs-
- D.A.R.E?

00:14:02.007 --> 00:14:02.925
- It was kind of like that

00:14:02.925 --> 00:14:04.218
from that era.
- Right.

00:14:04.218 --> 00:14:06.971
- And then like I think my
first television show was

00:14:06.971 --> 00:14:08.889
in "The Outsiders."

00:14:08.889 --> 00:14:11.100
There's my whole filmography.
- Wow.

00:14:11.100 --> 00:14:13.352
- That's my whole, that's my whole.

00:14:13.352 --> 00:14:16.105
- Which brings me to one of my questions.

00:14:16.105 --> 00:14:20.359
PTA was your white whale for
a while after "Boogie Nights."

00:14:20.359 --> 00:14:22.236
Now you've just worked with him,

00:14:22.236 --> 00:14:23.612
who's your white whale now?

00:14:27.116 --> 00:14:27.950
- I don't know really.

00:14:27.950 --> 00:14:29.827
I mean there's a lot of
great directors out there.

00:14:29.827 --> 00:14:31.745
Damien Chazelle's very talented,

00:14:31.745 --> 00:14:35.332
Michael Mann's amazing, I've
always wanted to work with him.

00:14:35.332 --> 00:14:37.418
There's so many, I don't
really have one specifically

00:14:37.418 --> 00:14:38.752
if I'm being honest.

00:14:38.752 --> 00:14:41.130
Paul for me was always somebody

00:14:41.130 --> 00:14:44.341
who I kind of felt
generationally was somebody that

00:14:44.341 --> 00:14:45.301
I really looked up to.

00:14:45.301 --> 00:14:47.219
He almost did "Boogie Nights" together,

00:14:47.219 --> 00:14:50.347
and then I got to watch
his entire career progress

00:14:50.347 --> 00:14:52.892
over the last 25 years

00:14:52.892 --> 00:14:55.686
and see this incredible visionary

00:14:55.686 --> 00:14:58.063
and just always wanted
to do something with him.

00:14:58.063 --> 00:14:59.773
- Did you pass on "Boogie Nights?"

00:15:00.691 --> 00:15:02.735
- It was a hybrid of that.

00:15:04.320 --> 00:15:06.572
Like there was "Titanic"
and then there was-

00:15:06.572 --> 00:15:07.907
- Oh right.
- "Boogie Nights"

00:15:07.907 --> 00:15:10.534
and they kind of overlapped.

00:15:10.534 --> 00:15:11.785
Maybe it could have

00:15:11.785 --> 00:15:13.287
worked out-
- Have you rewatched

00:15:13.287 --> 00:15:14.455
"Titanic?"
- No.

00:15:14.455 --> 00:15:15.664
- Oh, you should.

00:15:15.664 --> 00:15:16.498
- I haven't seen it

00:15:16.498 --> 00:15:17.333
in forever.
- I bet you could-

00:15:17.333 --> 00:15:19.752
I bet you could like
watch it as a movie now.

00:15:19.752 --> 00:15:21.337
And it's so good.

00:15:21.337 --> 00:15:23.547
- I don't really watch, maybe I do,

00:15:23.547 --> 00:15:24.840
some movies I've watched.

00:15:24.840 --> 00:15:27.092
Do you watch your old, your movies a lot?

00:15:27.092 --> 00:15:30.179
- No, I've never made
something like "Titanic."

00:15:30.179 --> 00:15:32.681
But if I did I would watch it.

00:15:32.681 --> 00:15:33.599
- But I mean, do you put,

00:15:33.599 --> 00:15:35.392
when was the last time you did that?

00:15:36.352 --> 00:15:40.230
- When I was really drunk,
I put on "American Hustle"

00:15:41.649 --> 00:15:43.525
and then my assistant went
to download something-

00:15:43.525 --> 00:15:44.443
- But did you do it alone-
- the next day-

00:15:44.443 --> 00:15:46.111
- or were you showing some-

00:15:46.111 --> 00:15:47.780
- Showing people? Oh my God.
- Oh, being like,

00:15:47.780 --> 00:15:48.948
yo, this is what this movie

00:15:48.948 --> 00:15:50.240
was like.
- No, I was drunk

00:15:50.240 --> 00:15:52.493
and I was like, I wonder
if I'm good at acting

00:15:52.493 --> 00:15:54.203
and I put on "American Hustle"

00:15:54.203 --> 00:15:56.497
and I don't remember what the, what the,

00:15:56.497 --> 00:15:58.082
what the answer was.
- That is funny.

00:15:58.082 --> 00:16:00.209
- I'm gonna have them cut that out.

00:16:00.209 --> 00:16:01.877
- That is very funny.
- For sure.

00:16:03.087 --> 00:16:04.755
- I wanted to ask about David O. Russell.

00:16:04.755 --> 00:16:05.589
- [Jennifer] Oh, okay.

00:16:05.589 --> 00:16:07.675
- And what the first film was like,

00:16:07.675 --> 00:16:11.011
what "American Hustle" was
like, "Silver Linings,"

00:16:11.011 --> 00:16:14.765
and what you feel like
he brought out in you

00:16:14.765 --> 00:16:15.975
in a lot of these roles?

00:16:15.975 --> 00:16:18.394
I mean, I think you've
talked about it like-

00:16:18.394 --> 00:16:19.520
- Yeah.
- This sort of push and pull

00:16:19.520 --> 00:16:20.980
with him and, and-

00:16:20.980 --> 00:16:22.022
- I mean, I wanna be-
- How he helped you

00:16:22.022 --> 00:16:23.232
as an actor in a lot of ways.

00:16:23.232 --> 00:16:24.358
- Yeah. Yeah.

00:16:24.358 --> 00:16:26.610
And he taught me how to act really.

00:16:26.610 --> 00:16:29.571
I wanna be sensitive to the-
- That's hard to believe.

00:16:29.571 --> 00:16:31.448
- Other actors who've worked with him

00:16:31.448 --> 00:16:33.033
'cause I know he's tough, you know,

00:16:33.033 --> 00:16:35.828
and he can be really,
really hard on people.

00:16:36.912 --> 00:16:38.789
For me, I don't know if it was,

00:16:38.789 --> 00:16:40.916
'cause I like grew up doing sports

00:16:40.916 --> 00:16:44.586
and so I just felt like he
was just like a stern coach.

00:16:44.586 --> 00:16:45.546
- Right.
- You know, it's like,

00:16:45.546 --> 00:16:47.214
"Do it louder, do it more quiet.

00:16:47.214 --> 00:16:49.133
That was bullshit, do it again.

00:16:49.133 --> 00:16:50.718
That was bad, do it better."

00:16:50.718 --> 00:16:54.722
Like, it was just very
like straightforward to me.

00:16:54.722 --> 00:16:55.848
And I think I was young enough

00:16:55.848 --> 00:16:58.809
that I didn't have anything to,

00:16:58.809 --> 00:17:01.228
it was normal, like to me,

00:17:02.563 --> 00:17:06.066
'cause I was like 21 when I
did "Silver Linings Playbook,"

00:17:06.066 --> 00:17:07.860
it just felt really alive.

00:17:07.860 --> 00:17:09.653
I never felt like he
was like yelling at me.

00:17:09.653 --> 00:17:13.657
But anyway, I feel like when
I say he taught me how to act,

00:17:13.657 --> 00:17:17.661
I feel like because I
never did like lessons

00:17:17.661 --> 00:17:19.079
or anything like that,

00:17:19.079 --> 00:17:22.583
I think I would've really
easily fallen into,

00:17:22.583 --> 00:17:24.209
I don't know, something.

00:17:25.169 --> 00:17:30.090
And he, I mean, you know how
I'm like never like prepared

00:17:30.090 --> 00:17:32.092
and I would always feel bad-
- That's not true at all.

00:17:32.092 --> 00:17:32.968
- About that.

00:17:33.969 --> 00:17:35.637
But he was kind of like,

00:17:36.597 --> 00:17:39.767
he taught me that like,
that was like staying loose,

00:17:39.767 --> 00:17:40.642
and that, that's okay.

00:17:40.642 --> 00:17:44.813
And I think if I wasn't like
aware that sometimes there's,

00:17:44.813 --> 00:17:47.608
sometimes there's the need to like prepare

00:17:47.608 --> 00:17:50.527
and then sometimes there
is the need to like

00:17:50.527 --> 00:17:51.945
to not and to stay loose,

00:17:51.945 --> 00:17:52.780
and I'm happy he taught me that.

00:17:52.780 --> 00:17:54.364
- But you kinda like the process

00:17:54.364 --> 00:17:56.492
of somebody calling out
direction like that?

00:17:56.492 --> 00:17:57.534
- Yeah.
- You do?

00:17:57.534 --> 00:17:58.744
- Interesting.
- Do you?

00:17:58.744 --> 00:17:59.578
You don't?

00:17:59.578 --> 00:18:01.038
- I think it does help sometimes.

00:18:01.038 --> 00:18:02.915
- Yeah.
- Actually.

00:18:02.915 --> 00:18:06.293
- But you show up like
you're already like,

00:18:08.045 --> 00:18:09.630
you're like making the movie.

00:18:09.630 --> 00:18:11.006
- But the idea of somebody, I mean,

00:18:11.006 --> 00:18:14.718
yeah, I'm trying to think
if I ever had that. Yeah.

00:18:14.718 --> 00:18:15.886
Most, 'cause most of the times

00:18:15.886 --> 00:18:17.429
it's the director coming up to you

00:18:17.429 --> 00:18:19.556
in an intimate conversation like that.

00:18:19.556 --> 00:18:22.142
- Yeah, and I really don't
like being tiptoed around,

00:18:22.142 --> 00:18:25.062
like I'm an emotional
landmine, I hate that.

00:18:25.062 --> 00:18:26.563
(dogs barking)

00:18:26.563 --> 00:18:27.648
- Just gonna leave it?

00:18:28.649 --> 00:18:29.483
- Its your girlfriend,

00:18:29.483 --> 00:18:30.734
you clean it up.
- Nice.

00:18:31.860 --> 00:18:33.737
- She pissed on the floor too.

00:18:33.737 --> 00:18:36.949
- For this movie, did you
have that dynamic too?

00:18:36.949 --> 00:18:38.951
- For this movie she was really hands off

00:18:38.951 --> 00:18:41.036
by the time we started shooting.

00:18:41.036 --> 00:18:44.873
She kind of like builds the
world and then steps back,

00:18:44.873 --> 00:18:47.543
and like watches and
is very observational.

00:18:47.543 --> 00:18:50.754
But I think like our conversations
were, it was like more

00:18:50.754 --> 00:18:54.424
of a universal conversation than like a

00:18:54.424 --> 00:18:56.343
coming up in between.

00:18:56.343 --> 00:18:58.887
- And a lot of it was
improvised obviously, right?

00:18:58.887 --> 00:18:59.763
- I don't think

00:18:59.763 --> 00:19:00.597
we did that much.
- Was that written

00:19:00.597 --> 00:19:01.890
in the script?

00:19:01.890 --> 00:19:03.809
All the stuff that you did in that film?

00:19:03.809 --> 00:19:06.937
- No, I mean for the like pacing
around the house and stuff,

00:19:06.937 --> 00:19:08.272
she would just kind of set up a camera

00:19:08.272 --> 00:19:09.690
and tell me to-

00:19:09.690 --> 00:19:10.566
- Exist.

00:19:10.566 --> 00:19:11.400
- Yeah.

00:19:11.400 --> 00:19:13.026
I think she improved a lot.

00:19:13.026 --> 00:19:15.028
Like us crawling in the grass

00:19:15.028 --> 00:19:17.573
that was written as like
us like flipping burgers

00:19:17.573 --> 00:19:19.283
when he proposes to me.

00:19:19.283 --> 00:19:20.701
- Didn't you say that was the first day

00:19:20.701 --> 00:19:21.743
of filming or something?

00:19:21.743 --> 00:19:25.122
- No, the first day was the
naked fighting like tigers.

00:19:25.122 --> 00:19:28.000
(Leonardo giggling)

00:19:28.000 --> 00:19:28.834
Yeah.

00:19:30.210 --> 00:19:32.129
And Rob and I didn't even
know each other that well,

00:19:32.129 --> 00:19:33.714
we like met a couple times.

00:19:33.714 --> 00:19:34.548
- [Leonardo] Wow.

00:19:34.548 --> 00:19:36.091
- I think it was better that way.

00:19:36.091 --> 00:19:38.760
- Like threw you into the
gauntlet, you kinda like that?

00:19:38.760 --> 00:19:39.595
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

00:19:39.595 --> 00:19:41.513
- I think so.
- Yeah.

00:19:41.513 --> 00:19:43.098
- Have you ever done nudity?

00:19:43.098 --> 00:19:44.975
- Full? Yes, maybe, I have.

00:19:45.809 --> 00:19:48.896
I did a film which you
never would've seen called,

00:19:48.896 --> 00:19:51.690
"Total Eclipse" about Arthur Rambo,

00:19:51.690 --> 00:19:54.735
French poet when I was 17 or 18.

00:19:54.735 --> 00:19:55.986
I was nude in that,

00:19:55.986 --> 00:19:58.614
and I think I was partially
nude in "Aviator."

00:19:58.614 --> 00:19:59.990
- Mm, you should rewatch it.

00:20:00.866 --> 00:20:03.869
(Leonardo and Jennifer laughing)

00:20:03.869 --> 00:20:06.914
- I was trying to get the
