00:30:39.045 --> 00:30:40.630
and everywhere we went,

00:30:40.630 --> 00:30:44.759
all sort of the local
community that we worked with

00:30:44.759 --> 00:30:47.512
really helped with shaping the whole movie

00:30:47.512 --> 00:30:48.680
and the narrative.

00:30:48.680 --> 00:30:50.598
A lot of the people we
worked with in the movie

00:30:50.598 --> 00:30:52.308
are non-actors.

00:30:52.308 --> 00:30:56.020
So he just bring people in that
really had those vocations.

00:30:56.020 --> 00:30:58.022
- Well, we're about to
work with each other.

00:30:58.022 --> 00:30:58.857
- Yeah.

00:30:58.857 --> 00:31:00.149
- Is there anything that I need to,

00:31:00.149 --> 00:31:02.610
like I should absolutely
know about Martin Scorsese

00:31:02.610 --> 00:31:03.528
before we start.

00:31:03.528 --> 00:31:04.863
- It's a great thing

00:31:04.863 --> 00:31:08.741
and he's gonna give you
a lot of film references.

00:31:08.741 --> 00:31:09.784
- Oh, do I have to watch

00:31:09.784 --> 00:31:10.827
all of them?
- Which is amazing,

00:31:10.827 --> 00:31:13.204
'cause they usually come
in the form of a DVD

00:31:13.204 --> 00:31:14.789
and if you don't have a DVD player,

00:31:14.789 --> 00:31:15.957
get a DVD player.
- Oh my god,

00:31:15.957 --> 00:31:17.667
I'm gonna kill myself.

00:31:17.667 --> 00:31:21.337
So, but he'll have
screenings sometimes for

00:31:21.337 --> 00:31:23.298
just one sequence in the movie.

00:31:23.298 --> 00:31:24.841
Like if he can't,

00:31:24.841 --> 00:31:27.093
he doesn't have a hard
time articulating anything,

00:31:27.093 --> 00:31:29.637
but if there's something
that he wants you to capture

00:31:29.637 --> 00:31:31.139
from an old film-
- Cool.

00:31:31.139 --> 00:31:33.349
- Or the pacing of something,

00:31:33.349 --> 00:31:35.518
you might have a screening of a whole film

00:31:35.518 --> 00:31:39.647
just for a specific scene that
he wants to try to capture.

00:31:39.647 --> 00:31:43.943
You know, we might see
some Japanese ghost films

00:31:43.943 --> 00:31:45.236
for reference.
- Cool.

00:31:45.236 --> 00:31:47.530
- Just to get the tone of it.

00:31:47.530 --> 00:31:48.865
You're gonna have an amazing time.

00:31:48.865 --> 00:31:50.158
- Wow.
- Yeah.

00:31:50.158 --> 00:31:52.160
- Are you really excited
to work with me again?

00:31:52.160 --> 00:31:53.411
- Yes, I am.
- I am too.

00:31:53.411 --> 00:31:55.330
- Are you really excited
to work with Marty

00:31:55.330 --> 00:31:56.289
for the first time?

00:31:57.332 --> 00:31:58.207
Who isn't, right?

00:31:58.207 --> 00:32:00.418
- I can't like believe that.

00:32:00.418 --> 00:32:02.003
Okay, Leo, well goodbye.

